initial_story:
The Eurovision Song Contest is just around the corner and this year, it's taking place in Malmo, Sweden.

You can find out all about the event right here.

The UK's entry for 2024 is Olly Alexander who'll be performing his song, Dizzy.

But how's he feeling ahead of the big night, where he'll perform in front of 200 million people!

De-Graft sat down with him to find out all about his preparation for the competition.

The Eurovision Song contest Grand Final will be shown on BBC One and iPlayer on Saturday 11 May.

The song is catchy, the choreography is slick, and I'm feeling like I'm in the best shape of my life vocally. I've been doing a lot of vocal warm-ups and exercises to make sure I'm giving it my all on the night. I'm also trying to stay relaxed and focused, you know, not get too caught up in the hype of it all. It's a big show, but I'm ready for it!"

"I've been visualizing the crowd's reaction, imagining the energy in the room when we perform 'You & I' for the first time. It's going to be electric, I can feel it. I've also been working on my stage presence, making sure I'm connecting with the audience and owning that stage. I want to make sure everyone leaves feeling like they've been a part of something special. And, of course, I'm excited to debut our new music video during the performance. It's going to be a wild ride!"

"The anticipation is building up inside me, I can barely sleep at night thinking about the show. I've been rehearsing non-stop, perfecting every note, every move. I want to make sure I'm giving the fans the best possible experience. And I know the band is feeling the same way, we've all been working tirelessly to get everything just right. I just hope the crowd will be as excited as I am when we take the stage. It's going to be a night to remember!"
